    "name": "Question 9 @ 2019/2020",
    "Question": {
      "content": "A capacitor must light a 50W bulb for 30mins at 200V. What capacitance is needed?",
      "type": "OBJ",
      "options": [
        "90F",
        "45F",
        "6F",
        "9F"
      ]
    },
    "Answer": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "45F"
    },
    "Explanation": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "Energy required: \\(E = P \\times t = 50W \\times 1800s = 90,000J\\) Capacitor energy: \\(E = \\frac{1}{2}CV^2 \\) \\(C = \\frac{2E}{V^2} = \\frac{2 \\times 90,000}{(200)^2} = 4.5F\\) (Note: 45F is likely a typo in options)"
    },
    "topic": [
