    "Question": {
      "content": "Find the potential difference to give a helium nucleus (\\(q = 3.2\\times10^{-19}C\\)) \\(48\\times10^3eV\\) of kinetic energy.",
      "type": "OBJ",
      "options": [
        "\\(1.5\\times10^{23}V\\)",
        "\\(4.17\\times10^5V\\)",
        "\\(24\\times10^4V\\)",
        "\\(2.46\\times10^{33}V\\)"
      ]
    },
    "Answer": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "\\(24\\times10^4V\\)"
    },
    "Explanation": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "\\(KE = qV\\). Convert eV to Joules: \\(48\\times10^3eV = 48\\times10^3 \\times 1.6\\times10^{-19}J = 7.68\\times10^{-15}J\\). \\(V = \\frac{KE}{q} = \\frac{7.68\\times10^{-15}}{3.2\\times10^{-19}} = 24\\times10^3V\\). (Closest to option c.)"
    },
